OL,3,CGovernment to back huge loan to JLR in
OL,4,Corder to save supply chain
OL,6,FRachel Reeves insisted she would
OL,7,F"stand up" for JLR, but her ability to
OL,8,Fextend support is greatly restricted
OL,9,Fby the state of the government's
OL,10,Ffinances.
OL,12,FAgreeing to back a loan to Jaguar Land
OL,13,FRover avoids the need for cash
OL,14,Fpayments upfront. The government is
OL,15,Fonly on the hook if JLR defaults -
OL,16,Fsomething which is incredibly unlikely
OL,17,Fgiven how well-resourced the company
OL,18,Fis. The risk to the Treasury is low,
OL,19,Fand arguably close to zero.
